{"title_page": "Weddings and Funerals", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{refimprove|date=January 2017}}\n{{notability|books|date=May 2015}}\n}}\n\n'''\"Weddings and Funerals\"''' is a [[nursery rhyme]] or [[traditional music|folksong]] and [[playground game]].\n\n:''A wedding song we played for you,''\n::''The dance you did but scorn.''\n:''A woeful dirge we chanted, too,''\n::''But then you would not mourn''.\n\n==Origin==\nThe verse is based on the verses {{bibleref|Matthew|11:17}} and {{bibleref|Luke|7:32}} in the [[New Testament]] of the Christian [[Bible]].\n\nThe exact words of this English nursery rhyme were incorporated as the translation of these verses in the [[International Standard Version]] (2008).<ref>[http://bible.cc/matthew/11-17.htm Matthew 11:17, parallel translations] at Biblos.com</ref>\n\nIn context, the verse was spoken by [[Jesus]] as a reproach to those people who rejected both the austere lifestyle and preaching of [[John the Baptist]] and his own more accessible ministry.<ref>[[Matthew Henry]]'s Commentary on Matthew 11:16-24, available online at [http://biblecommenter.com/matthew/11-17.htm BibleCommenter.com]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Portal|Children's literature}}\n\n[[Category:English nursery rhymes]]\n[[Category:English children's songs]]\n[[Category:English folk songs]]\n[[Category:Traditional children's songs]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of John the Baptist]]\n[[Category:New Testament words and phrases]]\n[[Category:Sayings of Jesus]]\n[[Category:Gospel of Matthew]]\n[[Category:Year of song unknown]]\n[[Category:Matthew 11]]\n[[Category:Songwriter unknown]]\n\n\n{{poem-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{refimprove|date=January 2017}}\n{{notability|books|date=May 2015}}\n}}\n\n'''\"Weddings and Funerals\"''' is a [[nursery rhyme]] or [[traditional music|folksong]] and [[playground game]].\n\n:''A wedding song we played for you,''\n::''The dance you did but scorn.''\n:''A woeful dirge we chanted, too,''\n::''But then you would not mourn''.\n\n==Origin==\nThe verse is based on the verses {{bibleref|Matthew|11:17}} and {{bibleref|Luke|7:32}} in the [[New Testament]] of the Christian [[Bible]].\n\nThe exact words of this English nursery rhyme were incorporated as the translation of these verses in the [[International Standard Version]] (2008).<ref>[http://bible.cc/matthew/11-17.htm Matthew 11:17, parallel translations] at Biblos.com</ref>\n\nIn context, the verse was spoken by [[Jesus]] as a reproach to those people who rejected both the austere lifestyle and preaching of [[John the Baptist]] and his own more accessible ministry.<ref>[[Matthew Henry]]'s Commentary on Matthew 11:16-24, available online at [http://biblecommenter.com/matthew/11-17.htm BibleCommenter.com]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Portal|Children's literature}}\n\n[[Category:English nursery rhymes]]\n[[Category:English children's songs]]\n[[Category:English folk songs]]\n[[Category:English-language songs]]\n[[Category:Traditional children's songs]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of John the Baptist]]\n[[Category:New Testament words and phrases]]\n[[Category:Sayings of Jesus]]\n[[Category:Gospel of Matthew]]\n[[Category:Year of song unknown]]\n[[Category:Matthew 11]]\n[[Category:Songwriter unknown]]\n\n\n{{poem-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Richhoncho", "label": "safe", "comment": "removedCategory:English-language songsusingHotCat- container cat.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weddings_and_Funerals"}
